        <trans-unit id="306" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the request form of the Post Inventory Cost to G/L the Closed Period Entry Posting Date field is available.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="307" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The program uses the date you enter in this field as the posting date for the general ledger entries it creates for value entries whose posting dates are in closed accounting periods.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="308" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Otherwise, the general ledger entries will have the same posting date as the original value entries.</source>
