        <trans-unit id="309" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>A date is considered to be in a closed period when it is earlier than the date in the Allow Posting From field in the General Ledger Setup.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="310" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>If posting to G<ph id="ph1">\/</ph>L Per Posting Group, the general ledger entries will have the posting date that is specified in the Posting Date field in the request form.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="311" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In version 3 and 4 the batch job scans all value entries to detect if there are any value entries where Cost Amount (Actual) differs from Cost Posted to G/L.</source>
